<title>NETHERLANDS: KLM to shed 960 jobs over three years - paper.</title>
<headline>KLM to shed 960 jobs over three years - paper.</headline>
<dateline>AMSTERDAM 1997-02-08</dateline>
<text>
<p>KLM Royal Dutch Airlines will shed around 960 jobs from a total of 22,000 over the next three years as part of its Focus 2000 restructuring programme, newspaper NRC Handelsblad said on Saturday.</p>
<p>The figure is made up of the 160 positions the company regarded as &quot;superfluous&quot; and 800 through the closure of services and parts of services, the paper said.</p>
<p>One of the main areas for cuts will be the company's head office in Amsterdam, where 340 of the 900 jobs will go.</p>
<p>KLM said last week its Focus 2000 programme was on target to boost operating income by 1.5 billion guilders in three years.</p>
<p>--Amsterdam Newsroom +31 20 504 5000</p>
